TITLE.0: GOES I-S (G08-G17) L2 Magnetometer (MAG) Geomagnetic Field 2 Hz Product with Complete Coordinate Frames

TEXT.0: Magnetometer high-resolution data for the GOES-8 through GOES-17, (GOES I-M, GOES-NOP and GOES-R series of 10 spacecraft). The GOES MAG subsystem consists of fluxgate magnetometer instruments monitoring three orthogonal components of the geomagnetic field at geosynchronous orbit (L = 6.6) with high resolution sampling rate (G8-15: 2 Hz and G16-17: 10 Hz). The NetCDF product files include the magnetometer observations from the instrument(s) in several coordinate systems, and the satellite location calculated using a standard SGP/SDP orbit propagator. The field measurements are provided as B field vectors in the ECI (Earth-centered inertial), EPN (earthward, poleward, normal/eastward), GSE (geocentric solar ecliptic), GSM(geocentric solar magnetospheric) and VDH (dipole aligned) coordinate systems. For comprehensive documentation including caveats and usage recommendations, please consult the GOES magnetometer User's Guide at NCEI.
